# ADR-003 — Workflow Before Automation

## Status

Accepted

## Date

2026-07-01

## Context

Many personal knowledge systems fail because they prioritize tools and automation before validating the underlying workflow.

Automation without a stable workflow increases complexity without delivering long-term value.

## Decision

Atlas will always validate a manual workflow before introducing automation.

The implementation order is:

1. Capture
2. Organize
3. Review
4. Automate

Features such as MCP, Dataview, Templater, and custom Agents will only be introduced after the corresponding manual workflow has proven useful.

## Consequences

### Positive

- Simpler onboarding.
- Better long-term architecture.
- Automation serves the workflow instead of defining it.

### Negative

- More manual work during the early stages.
